hxqwen32b.c is a native FFI shim (not a hexa compilation target).
It exists so Linux x86_64 hosts (2× H100 tensor-parallel) can link against
libhxqwen32b.so with the same ABI that Mac uses for libhxqwen32b.dylib —
symbol-for-symbol identical, so hexa @link("libhxqwen32b") code is
platform-agnostic at the source level.

Adapted from hxqwen14b.c v4. Differs only in QWEN32B_N_LAYER=64 and
QWEN32B_FFN_DIM=27648 per H11 Qwen2.5-32B audit. LoRA target count is
bumped to 7 (q,k,v,o,gate,up,down) = 448 adapters for 64 layers.

Do not transpile, do not include in the stage0 pipeline. Compiled
only by tool/build_hxqwen32b_linux.hexa.
